{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-15257/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-15257"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:52:57"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Woman's hand chopping mushroom"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-15257","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-15257"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/canvas/1/bc117f00-9de9-41eb-9287-eb55ac4780d8","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:38:26.706Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The way Alma cuts the mushrooms can be read in numerous ways. It is sensual in how she handles the fungi; throughout the film, of course, food has been closely associated with Reynolds’s hunger (for food and for sex). The close-up also parallels other shots of Reynolds and his seamstresses at work on dresses, so Alma’s cooking (poisoning) is an artistic act, one rooted in destruction and disruption rather than creation as such. The slicing of the mushroom is rather mundane, but given the circumstances, it exudes a certain violence, as the act of cooking dinner represents the anger and frustration she feels toward Reynolds.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15257/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:227.95604066985646,169.39593301435409,1139.4796650717701,582.9747308612439"}}}]}]}]}